HEADWORD: Foulard
<hw>Fou`lard"</hw> <pr>(f. f⟦oomac⟧`l⟦adot⟧r"; E.
f⟦oomac⟧`l⟦aum⟧rd")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A thin, washable material of silk, or silk and cotton, usually with
a printed pattern on it. It was originally imported from India, but now
also made elsewhere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an article of clothing made of <er>foulard{1}</er>,
such as a neckpiece.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foulder</ent>⟦br⟧
